docstring:
"""
    A wrapper for the OGRSpatialReference object. According to the GDAL web site,
    the SpatialReference object "provide[s] services to represent coordinate
    systems (projections and datums) and to transform between them."
    """
name: SpatialReference

methods.docstring:
"""
        Create a GDAL OSR Spatial Reference object from the given input.
        The input may be string of OGC Well Known Text (WKT), an integer
        EPSG code, a PROJ string, and/or a projection "well known" shorthand
        string (one of 'WGS84', 'WGS72', 'NAD27', 'NAD83').
        """
methods.name: __init__

methods.docstring:
"""
        Return the value of the given string attribute node, None if the node
        doesn't exist.  Can also take a tuple as a parameter, (target, child),
        where child is the index of the attribute in the WKT.  For example:

        >>> wkt = 'GEOGCS["WGS 84", DATUM["WGS_1984, ... AUTHORITY["EPSG","4326"]]'
        >>> srs = SpatialReference(wkt) # could also use 'WGS84', or 4326
        >>> print(srs['GEOGCS'])
        WGS 84
        >>> print(srs['DATUM'])
        WGS_1984
        >>> print(srs['AUTHORITY'])
        EPSG
        >>> print(srs['AUTHORITY', 1]) # The authority value
        4326
        >>> print(srs['TOWGS84', 4]) # the fourth value in this wkt
        0
        >>> print(srs['UNIT|AUTHORITY']) # For the units authority, have to use the pipe symbole.
        EPSG
        >>> print(srs['UNIT|AUTHORITY', 1]) # The authority value for the units
        9122
        """
methods.name: __getitem__

methods.docstring: "Use 'pretty' WKT."
methods.name: __str__

methods.docstring:
"""
        The attribute value for the given target node (e.g. 'PROJCS'). The index
        keyword specifies an index of the child node to return.
        """
methods.name: attr_value

methods.docstring: "Return the authority name for the given string target node."
methods.name: auth_name

methods.docstring: "Return the authority code for the given string target node."
methods.name: auth_code

methods.docstring: "Return a clone of this SpatialReference object."
methods.name: clone

methods.docstring: "Morph this SpatialReference from ESRI's format to EPSG."
methods.name: from_esri

methods.docstring:
"""
        This method inspects the WKT of this SpatialReference, and will
        add EPSG authority nodes where an EPSG identifier is applicable.
        """
methods.name: identify_epsg

methods.docstring: "Morph this SpatialReference to ESRI's format."
methods.name: to_esri

methods.docstring: "Check to see if the given spatial reference is valid."
methods.name: validate

methods.docstring: "Return the name of this Spatial Reference."
methods.name: name

methods.docstring: "Return the SRID of top-level authority, or None if undefined."
methods.name: srid

methods.docstring: "Return the name of the linear units."
methods.name: linear_name

methods.docstring: "Return the value of the linear units."
methods.name: linear_units

methods.docstring: "Return the name of the angular units."
methods.name: angular_name

methods.docstring: "Return the value of the angular units."
methods.name: angular_units

methods.docstring:
"""
        Return a 2-tuple of the units value and the units name. Automatically
        determine whether to return the linear or angular units.
        """
methods.name: units

methods.docstring:
"""
        Return a tuple of the ellipsoid parameters:
         (semimajor axis, semiminor axis, and inverse flattening)
        """
methods.name: ellipsoid

methods.docstring: "Return the Semi Major Axis for this Spatial Reference."
methods.name: semi_major

methods.docstring: "Return the Semi Minor Axis for this Spatial Reference."
methods.name: semi_minor

methods.docstring: "Return the Inverse Flattening for this Spatial Reference."
methods.name: inverse_flattening

methods.docstring:
"""
        Return True if this SpatialReference is geographic
         (root node is GEOGCS).
        """
methods.name: geographic

methods.docstring: "Return True if this SpatialReference is local (root node is LOCAL_CS)."
methods.name: local

methods.docstring:
"""
        Return True if this SpatialReference is a projected coordinate system
         (root node is PROJCS).
        """
methods.name: projected

methods.docstring: "Import the Spatial Reference from the EPSG code (an integer)."
methods.name: import_epsg

methods.docstring: """Import the Spatial Reference from a PROJ string."""
methods.name: import_proj

methods.docstring: "Import the Spatial Reference from the given user input string."
methods.name: import_user_input

methods.docstring: "Import the Spatial Reference from OGC WKT (string)"
methods.name: import_wkt

methods.docstring: "Import the Spatial Reference from an XML string."
methods.name: import_xml

methods.docstring: "Return the WKT representation of this Spatial Reference."
methods.name: wkt

methods.docstring: "Return the 'pretty' representation of the WKT."
methods.name: pretty_wkt

methods.docstring: """Return the PROJ representation for this Spatial Reference."""
methods.name: proj

methods.docstring: "Alias for proj()."
methods.name: proj4

methods.docstring: "Return the XML representation of this Spatial Reference."
methods.name: xml
